{"key":"processedPost-13801939","value":{"id":13801939,"first":13801340,"last":13801939,"when":1295292891,"utime":"01/17/11 09:34 PM","content":"In addition to the answers above, never use a bottom casing layer.&nbsp; That old so-called 'tek' was written by some noob, who has long since gone back to smoking crack.&nbsp; The casing layer if used, goes on top.&nbsp; However, cubensis benefits little from being cased and it just adds another step to go wrong.<br /><br />I'd suggest starting off with the basic <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek</a>, and then moving up from there to uncased bulk substrates after you learn the basics.<br />RR","title":"Re: casing","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}